Lab 12: Network Analysis using Cytoscape and RCy3

Basic Data Visualization Tutorial

Example of a default network from cytoscape. The data used are from yeast in which GAL1, GAL4, and GAL80 genes were perturbed.

Here we set the node fill color of the gal80Rexp to a gradient ranging from blue to red.

Here we set the default node color to a dark-grey color (originally blue).

Here we set the node border width to 10 for anything with significance value less than 0.05

Here we created a legend to indicate node fill color and node border width

Here we changed the layout to a degree sorted circle layout.

Here we converted the layout to a prefuse force-directed layout.

Here we selected nodes that were 2 or higher (highlighted yellow).

Here we expanded the nodes to include nearest neighbors to the previous network and then created a new network.
